QUESTION NO: 1
An insurance company needs data in order to do ad-hoc queries of quarterly trends. What data
store would BEST support these queries?
A. Metadata
B. Operational Data Store
C. Transactional systems
D. Data Mart
Answer: D
QUESTION NO: 2
A clothing retailer has accumulated customer information over a number of years through growth
and acquisition. Which of the following Business Intelligence tools is most appropriate for
cleansing the mailing list?
A. Ascential Integrity
B. Intelligent Miner
C. Information Integrator
D. ETI*Extract
Answer: A
QUESTION NO: 3
Which of the following is the LEAST important function of a project plan for a Business Intelligence
solution?
A. Provides an implementation road map to achieve the business goals and objectives
B. Serves as a communication vehicle for the project team
C. Serves as the basis for a disaster recovery plan
D. Establishes the scope, definition and assignment of project responsibilities
Answer: C

QUESTION NO: 5
A consultant has been asked to review an existing Business Intelligence solution for scalability
issues. Which of the following is the most important consideration?
A. Heterogeneous operational data sources
B. Backup and recovery techniques
C. Memory, CPU, and disk capacity of server
D. Client desktop configurations

QUESTION NO: 6
When designing a Business Intelligence solution, how should the Information Technology
organization be primarily involved?
A. provide capacity requirements
B. provide the skills and knowledge to build a Business Intelligence solution
C. define the business critical success factors
D. provide business rules to be used in the warehouse
Answer: B
QUESTION NO: 7

D. Amount of data analyzed for reports

QUESTION NO: 8
A fact table in a star schema database typically contains which elements?
A. Metadata, maintained for the purpose of operating or using the data warehouse
B. Security, authorization level for each end user
C. Descriptive attributes, used to put the facts in context
D. Measurements, typically numeric and additive
Answer: D
QUESTION NO: 9
A major telecommunications provider wishes to identify which of its current customers may soon
switch to an alternative provider. How can they support a marketing program designed to retain
those customers deemed most likely to move their business to the competition?
A. Build a mining base clustering active customers by their buying patterns
B. Perform demographic analysis for customers for each geographic region
C. Create a set of multi-dimensional profiles that summarize the characteristics of prior customers
that have switched
D. Build a multi-dimensional profile of the competition's customers and their offerings
Answer: C

A. use the DB2 Performance Expert
B. use the DB2 Governor
C. use the DB2 Health Monitor
D. rebind the DB2 plan with parallel DEGREE = ANY
Answer: B
